race.description: Thank You Long & Life Members Handicap (Bm60)
race.comment: A race that's likely to be hit by key scratchings. KINGSLAND (1) has raced a short price favourite his last three and delivered this grade/trip at Warwick last time. Maps well and only has to hold that form to be hard to beat. The Currie yard has three who can potentially go around. DECIMUS (3) resumed at big odds at the Sunshine Coast and was beaten just 2L after settling last. May need longer now but he ran a strong number and will get every chance from an inside gate. From the same stable PUROSANGUE (4) led over this trip and spaced the 55 graders by almost 6L at Kilcoy quickly back on track. The 2kg claimer can control the race and a bold effort is likely. CEEKAY'S CHOICE (6) would be a hope if she gave her best.
